       scrolling = {
-        column_width = 1.0 / 3;
-        explicit_column_widths = "0.25, ${toString (1.0 / 3)}, 0.4, 0.5, ${toString (2.0 / 3)}, 1.0";
+        column_width = "0.333333";
+        explicit_column_widths = "0.25, 0.333333, 0.4, 0.5, 0.666667, 1.0";","path":"home/hyprland.nix","commit_id":"1e28cd659fac4d1ca054fe151d80b9e976095c61","original_commit_id":"1e28cd659fac4d1ca054fe151d80b9e976095c61","user":{"login":"gemini-code-assist[bot]","id":176961590,"node_id":"BOT_kgDOCow4Ng","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/in/956858?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/gemini-code-assist%5Bbot%5D","html_url":"https://github.com/apps/gemini-code-assist","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gemini-code-assist%5Bbot%5D/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gemini-code-assist%5Bbot%5D/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gemini-code-assist%5Bbot%5D/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gemini-code-assist%5Bbot%5D/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gemini-code-assist%5Bbot%5D/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gemini-code-assist%5Bbot%5D/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gemini-code-assist%5Bbot%5D/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gemini-code-assist%5Bbot%5D/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gemini-code-assist%5Bbot%5D/received_events","type":"Bot","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

The change to use string literals for `column_width` and `explicit_column_widths` correctly addresses the 'Imprecise conversion from float to string' warnings. However, the values `0.333333` and `0.666667` are hardcoded approximations of `1/3` and `2/3`. While this is likely sufficient for UI layout, consider adding a comment to clarify their origin for future maintainers, or if Nix allows, defining them as named constants to improve readability and centralize precision control.","created_at":"2026-03-24T22:55:14Z","updated_at":"2026-03-24T22:55:14Z","html_url":"https://github.com/patflynn/cosmo/pull/379#discussion_r2984789614","pull_request_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/patflynn/cosmo/pulls/379","_links":{"self":{"href":"https://api.github.com/repos/patflynn/cosmo/pulls/comments/2984789614"},"html":{"href":"https://github.com/patflynn/cosmo/pull/379#discussion_r2984789614"},"pull_request":{"href":"https://api.github.com/repos/patflynn/cosmo/pulls/379"}},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/patflynn/cosmo/pulls/comments/2984789614/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"start_line":148,"original_start_line":148,"start_side":"RIGHT","line":149,"original_line":149,"side":"RIGHT","author_association":"NONE","original_position":7,"position":7,"subject_type":"line"}]

